   combined with moderate heat pain to yield a factorial design with factor
   `pain' as somatic stressor and factor `faces' as nonpainful psychosocial
   stressor. Pain responsive regions of interest in the insula, SII cortex,
   and thalamus were activated by the factor `faces' to a various extent.
